# No Code Comments

Do not add comments to source code in this repository.

This includes:
- `//` single-line comments
- `/* */` block comments
- `///` XML documentation comments
- `#region` / `#endregion` used only for organization

Write self-explanatory code instead: clear names, small functions, and straightforward structure.

## When editing existing code

- Do not add new comments
- Remove comments you touch when making related edits
- Do not add XML docs to public APIs

## Exceptions

Only add a comment when the user explicitly asks for one, or when required by an external tool (e.g. a suppression attribute that must name a rule ID).

Markdown documentation files (`README.md`, `PUBLISHING.md`) are not source code — updating those is fine.
